WEBVTT



00:00:00.128 --> 00:00:10.176
Life for women can be difficult. For mothers in the Central African Republic, it's a daily struggle for survival. Imagine navigating motherhood,

00:00:09.696 --> 00:00:16.960
While facing violence, forced marriage and barriers to education for yourself and for your children.

00:00:16.736 --> 00:00:26.784
This is the reality of living in extreme poverty. With your support, Tearfund can help women learn to read and write so they can earn a living and send their children home.

00:00:26.304 --> 00:00:34.272
A children to school, we're determined to end extreme poverty and injustice following Jesus where the need is greatest.

00:00:34.080 --> 00:00:36.192
Do you have a heart to help?

00:00:36.096 --> 00:00:40.288
Find out more at tearfund.org/premiere

00:00:41.024 --> 00:00:50.400
Hello friends, I'm Rick Warren and welcome to Spurgeon's Sermons. This is the official podcast brought to you by Premier and Spurgeon's College.

00:00:50.400 --> 00:01:00.448
You know the teachings of Charles Spurgeon have had a personal impact on my life in a profound way and I'm confident they'll do the same for you. So get ready to be challenged.

00:00:59.968 --> 00:01:08.704
be challenged, equipped, and guided by Charles Spurgeon, who is universally regarded as the greatest English preacher in the history of the Church.

00:01:09.824 --> 00:01:11.648
Silver sockets

00:01:11.616 --> 00:01:14.048
Or redemption the foundation.

00:01:14.112 --> 00:01:16.384
The sermon by Charles Spurgeon

00:01:16.704 --> 00:01:17.952
Part two.

00:01:19.520 --> 00:01:26.240
And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying, When thou takest the sum of the children of Israel after their number,

00:01:26.560 --> 00:01:33.088
Then shall they give every man a ransom for his soul unto the Lord, when thou numberest them.

00:01:33.536 --> 00:01:36.256
That there be no plague among them.

00:01:36.256 --> 00:01:38.016
When there are numbers, them.

00:01:38.432 --> 00:01:43.552
This they shall give, every one that passeth among them that are numbered.

00:01:43.328 --> 00:01:44.736
Half a shekel.

00:01:44.928 --> 00:01:47.328
After the shekel of the sanctuary.

00:01:47.488 --> 00:01:50.272
The shekel is twenty geras.

00:01:51.104 --> 00:01:54.464
And half shekel shall be the offering of the Lord.

00:01:54.656 --> 00:01:58.272
Everyone that passeth among them that are numbered,

00:01:58.016 --> 00:02:00.640
From 20 years old and above,

00:02:00.640 --> 00:02:03.232
Shall give an offering unto the Lord.

00:02:03.680 --> 00:02:06.272
The rich shall not give more,

00:02:06.496 --> 00:02:10.496
And the poor shall not give less than half a shekel.

00:02:10.496 --> 00:02:14.368
When they give an offering unto the Lord, to make an atonement,

00:02:14.304 --> 00:02:15.744
For your souls.

00:02:16.608 --> 00:02:20.960
And thou shalt take the atonement money of the children of Israel,

00:02:20.768 --> 00:02:25.216
And shall appoint it for the service of the tabernacle of the congregation.

00:02:25.888 --> 00:02:30.656
That it may be a memorial unto the children of Israel before the Lord.

00:02:30.432 --> 00:02:33.760
To make an atonement for your souls.

00:02:34.432 --> 00:02:36.736
Exodus chapter 30

00:02:36.608 --> 00:02:38.912
11 to 16.

00:02:40.160 --> 00:02:44.064
A becker for every man, that is half a shekel,

00:02:44.032 --> 00:02:46.304
After the shekel of the sanctuary,

00:02:46.208 --> 00:02:48.768
For everyone that went to be numbered.

00:02:48.800 --> 00:02:51.168
From 20 years old and upward,

00:02:51.296 --> 00:02:56.192
For 603,550 men.

00:02:56.736 --> 00:02:59.968
And of the hundred talents of silver were cast,

00:02:59.680 --> 00:03:02.080
The sockets of the sanctuary.

00:03:02.112 --> 00:03:04.160
And the sockets of the veil.

00:03:04.352 --> 00:03:07.616
And 100 sockets of the 100 talents

00:03:07.616 --> 00:03:09.952
A talent for a socket.

00:03:10.656 --> 00:03:13.120
Exodus chapter 38

00:03:13.152 --> 00:03:15.776
Verses 26 to 27.

00:03:17.280 --> 00:03:20.416
Now we turn to the second of our texts.

00:03:20.512 --> 00:03:23.744
And there we learn a very remarkable fact.

00:03:24.320 --> 00:03:28.000
In the 38th chapter verse 25

00:03:28.096 --> 00:03:32.096
We find that this mass of silver which was paid

00:03:32.064 --> 00:03:37.920
Whereby 603,550 men were redeemed,

00:03:37.888 --> 00:03:40.736
Each one paying his half shekel

00:03:40.640 --> 00:03:43.264
Came to a great weight of silver.

00:03:44.160 --> 00:03:47.424
It must have weighed something over four tons.

00:03:47.776 --> 00:03:51.808
And this was dedicated to the use of the tabernacle.

00:03:52.224 --> 00:03:55.424
The special application of the precious metal

00:03:55.616 --> 00:03:57.504
Was to make sockets

00:03:57.440 --> 00:04:02.720
into which the boards which made the walls of the tabernacle should be placed.

00:04:03.520 --> 00:04:05.280
The mass of silver,

00:04:05.216 --> 00:04:07.872
Made up 100 talents.

00:04:08.288 --> 00:04:12.768
And these upheld the 50 boards of the holy place.

00:04:13.184 --> 00:04:19.136
They were in the wilderness, constantly moving and continually shifting the tabernacle.

00:04:19.744 --> 00:04:20.736
Now,

00:04:20.480 --> 00:04:23.712
They might have dug out a foundation in the sand.

00:04:23.904 --> 00:04:26.368
Or on coming to a piece of rock

00:04:26.240 --> 00:04:28.000
Where they could not dig,

00:04:28.032 --> 00:04:30.816
They might have cut out foundations.

00:04:30.688 --> 00:04:32.256
With great toil.

00:04:33.216 --> 00:04:38.432
But the Lord appointed that they should carry the foundation of the tabernacle with them.

00:04:39.072 --> 00:04:40.928
A talent of silver,

00:04:40.896 --> 00:04:44.928
weighing I suppose close upon one hundred pounds

00:04:44.800 --> 00:04:48.224
Was either formed into the shape of a wedge,

00:04:48.608 --> 00:04:50.976
So as to be driven into the soil,

00:04:51.136 --> 00:04:54.496
Or else made into a solid square plate

00:04:54.400 --> 00:04:55.840
To lie upon it.

00:04:56.768 --> 00:04:58.848
In the wedge or plate

00:04:58.816 --> 00:05:00.640
Were made mortises.

00:05:00.416 --> 00:05:04.288
Into which the tenons of the boards could be readily fitted.

00:05:04.736 --> 00:05:06.816
These plates of silver,

00:05:06.656 --> 00:05:08.896
Fitted the one into the other.

00:05:09.184 --> 00:05:11.360
Tenon and Mortis wise.

00:05:10.880 --> 00:05:17.312
And thus they made a compact parallelogram, strengthened at the corners with double plates,

00:05:17.184 --> 00:05:21.952
And formed one foundation, movable when taken to pieces,

00:05:21.856 --> 00:05:24.256
Yet very secure as a whole.

00:05:24.864 --> 00:05:28.672
This foundation was made of the redemption money.

00:05:30.112 --> 00:05:32.352
See the instructive emblem.

00:05:32.576 --> 00:05:36.320
The foundation of the worship of Israel was redemption.

00:05:36.960 --> 00:05:39.872
The dwelling place of the Lord their God,

00:05:39.808 --> 00:05:42.176
Was founded on atonement.

00:05:42.752 --> 00:05:45.760
All the boards of incorruptible wood,

00:05:45.632 --> 00:05:47.552
And precious gold.

00:05:47.328 --> 00:05:50.080
stood upon the redemption price.

00:05:50.272 --> 00:05:52.992
And the curtains of fine linen

00:05:52.864 --> 00:05:55.840
And the veil of matchless workmanship,

00:05:55.872 --> 00:05:57.888
And the whole structure

00:05:57.760 --> 00:05:59.968
Rested on nothing else.

00:05:59.968 --> 00:06:05.856
But the solid mass of silver which had been paid as the redemption money of the people.

00:06:06.912 --> 00:06:09.152
There was only one exception.

00:06:09.152 --> 00:06:11.424
And that was at the door.

00:06:11.840 --> 00:06:14.784
Where was the entrance to the holy place?

00:06:14.752 --> 00:06:15.840
There,

00:06:15.648 --> 00:06:18.912
The pillars were set upon sockets of brass.

00:06:19.456 --> 00:06:21.312
Perhaps because

00:06:21.088 --> 00:06:24.544
As there was much going in and out of the priests,

00:06:24.640 --> 00:06:28.960
It was not meet that they should tread upon the token of redemption.

00:06:30.048 --> 00:06:32.480
The blood of the paschal lamb

00:06:32.704 --> 00:06:35.104
When Israel came out of Egypt,

00:06:35.008 --> 00:06:37.440
Was sprinkled on the lintel.

00:06:37.440 --> 00:06:39.808
And on the two side posts,

00:06:40.000 --> 00:06:41.696
But out of reverence,

00:06:41.632 --> 00:06:42.880
To that blood,

00:06:43.328 --> 00:06:46.208
It was not to be sprinkled on the threshold.

00:06:46.912 --> 00:06:50.240
Everything was done to show the atonement.

00:06:50.016 --> 00:06:54.080
is to be the precious foundation of all holy things.

00:06:54.400 --> 00:06:55.840
And to prevent

00:06:55.584 --> 00:06:58.176
A slighting or disregard of it.

00:06:58.656 --> 00:07:02.752
Woe unto that man of whom it shall ever be said.

00:07:02.912 --> 00:07:06.176
He hath trodden under foot the son of God.

00:07:06.144 --> 00:07:09.056
And hath counted the blood of the covenant,

00:07:08.768 --> 00:07:12.480
Wherewith he was sanctified an unholy thing.

00:07:13.824 --> 00:07:20.096
I do not for a moment bring before you the type of the text as a proof of doctrine.

00:07:20.544 --> 00:07:22.592
But I intend to use it,

00:07:22.400 --> 00:07:24.640
Simply as an illustration.

00:07:25.184 --> 00:07:28.896
It seems to me to be a very striking fool.

00:07:28.736 --> 00:07:30.848
And suggestive emblem.

00:07:31.200 --> 00:07:33.568
Setting forth most clearly,

00:07:33.312 --> 00:07:35.680
Certain precious truths

00:07:36.160 --> 00:07:40.192
I feel I am quite safe in using this illustration.

00:07:40.288 --> 00:07:42.080
Because it is one,

00:07:41.856 --> 00:07:44.608
Among a group of acknowledged types

00:07:44.736 --> 00:07:47.872
And could not have been given without reason.

00:07:48.896 --> 00:07:50.432
I do not see

00:07:50.240 --> 00:07:53.920
Why they could not have made the foundation sockets of iron.

00:07:54.048 --> 00:07:56.960
Or why they could not have been content,

00:07:56.544 --> 00:07:57.184
28, with

00:07:56.704 --> 00:07:59.168
With tent pins and cords.

00:07:59.008 --> 00:08:01.536
As in other cases of tent building.

00:08:01.792 --> 00:08:03.424
I see no reason.

00:08:03.264 --> 00:08:05.600
In the necessity of the case,

00:08:05.600 --> 00:08:08.672
Why, they must be sockets of silver.

00:08:08.960 --> 00:08:11.680
There must have been another reason.

00:08:12.640 --> 00:08:16.096
Why was that particular silver prescribed?

00:08:16.608 --> 00:08:17.984
Why must?

00:08:17.760 --> 00:08:21.440
The redemption money be used and nothing else.

00:08:21.792 --> 00:08:25.600
Surely there is teaching here if we will but see it.

00:08:27.136 --> 00:08:29.952
Moreover, this does not stand alone.

00:08:30.176 --> 00:08:33.664
For when the tabernacle was succeeded by the temple,

00:08:33.856 --> 00:08:37.696
Redemption was still conspicuous in the foundation.

00:08:38.944 --> 00:08:41.440
What was the foundation of the temple?

00:08:41.920 --> 00:08:43.232
It was the rock.

00:08:43.328 --> 00:08:44.960
Of Mount Moriah.

00:08:45.696 --> 00:08:47.968
And what was the hill of Moriah?

00:08:48.000 --> 00:08:49.504
But the place,

00:08:49.312 --> 00:08:53.216
where redemption and atonement had been set forth.

00:08:54.240 --> 00:08:55.520
It was there.

00:08:55.392 --> 00:08:58.816
that Abraham drew the knife to slay Isaac.

00:08:59.552 --> 00:09:03.296
A fair picture of the father offering up his son.

00:09:04.096 --> 00:09:05.920
It was there, the ram.

00:09:05.792 --> 00:09:09.728
Was caught in the thicket and was killed instead of Isaac.

00:09:10.080 --> 00:09:11.712
A fit emblem

00:09:11.552 --> 00:09:15.296
Of the substitute accepted instead of man.

00:09:16.192 --> 00:09:17.568
Later still.

00:09:17.376 --> 00:09:24.352
It was on Mount Moriah that the angel, when David attempted to number the people without redemption money,

00:09:24.320 --> 00:09:26.848
Stood with his sword drawn.

00:09:27.744 --> 00:09:30.944
There David offered sacrifices.

00:09:30.720 --> 00:09:32.704
And burned offerings.

00:09:33.280 --> 00:09:35.328
The offering was accepted.

00:09:35.456 --> 00:09:38.304
And the angel sheathed his sword.

00:09:38.880 --> 00:09:40.416
Another picture

00:09:40.416 --> 00:09:42.816
Of that power of redemption.

00:09:42.848 --> 00:09:46.464
By which mercy rejoices against judgment.

00:09:47.488 --> 00:09:48.640
I'm there.

00:09:48.736 --> 00:09:51.648
The Lord uttered the memorable sentence.

00:09:51.648 --> 00:09:52.992
It is enough.

00:09:53.152 --> 00:09:55.360
Stay now thine hand,

00:09:56.480 --> 00:09:58.016
This enough.

00:09:58.240 --> 00:10:00.576
Is the crown of redemption.

00:10:00.992 --> 00:10:04.384
Even as the great sacrifice himself said.

00:10:04.320 --> 00:10:05.952
It is finished

00:10:06.848 --> 00:10:10.816
So does the great acceptor of the sacrifice say,

00:10:10.816 --> 00:10:11.808
Enough.

00:10:13.120 --> 00:10:16.512
What a place of redemption was the hill of Zion!

00:10:17.472 --> 00:10:22.880
Now if the temple was built on a mount which must have been specially selected

00:10:22.752 --> 00:10:26.592
Because there the types of redemption were most plentiful.

00:10:27.008 --> 00:10:29.568
I feel that without an apology

00:10:29.664 --> 00:10:32.992
I may boldly take this first fact

00:10:32.800 --> 00:10:36.096
That the building of the tabernacle in the wilderness

00:10:36.000 --> 00:10:39.424
Was based and grounded upon redemption money.

00:10:39.552 --> 00:10:40.800
And use it

00:10:40.800 --> 00:10:42.496
For our instruction.

00:10:43.040 --> 00:10:45.312
With this much of preface

00:10:45.216 --> 00:10:49.248
We will now fall to and feed upon the spiritual meal

00:10:49.184 --> 00:10:51.104
Which is set before us.

00:10:51.936 --> 00:10:53.568
O for grace!

00:10:53.472 --> 00:10:57.952
To feast upon the heavenly bread that we may grow thereby,

00:10:57.824 --> 00:11:02.208
Spirit of the Living God, be pleased to help us in this matter.

00:11:03.264 --> 00:11:04.352
First.

00:11:04.896 --> 00:11:07.680
I want you to view this illustration

00:11:07.552 --> 00:11:12.320
As teaching us something about God in relation to humanity.

00:11:12.800 --> 00:11:14.784
The tent in the wilderness

00:11:14.656 --> 00:11:18.464
was typical of God's coming down to humanity.

00:11:18.400 --> 00:11:20.736
To hold commune with them.

00:11:21.344 --> 00:11:23.424
The fiery cloudy pillar,

00:11:23.392 --> 00:11:25.344
Visible outside

00:11:25.280 --> 00:11:31.360
And the bright light of the Shekinah visible to him, who was called to enter once a year.

00:11:31.296 --> 00:11:33.568
Into the innermost sanctuary.

00:11:33.632 --> 00:11:35.904
Shining over the mercy seat.

00:11:36.288 --> 00:11:42.592
These were the tokens of the special presence of the deity in the centre of the camp of Israel.

00:11:43.328 --> 00:11:45.952
The Lord seems to teach us

00:11:45.856 --> 00:11:49.088
In relation to his dealing with men and women,

00:11:49.248 --> 00:11:52.448
That he will meet them in the way of grace,

00:11:52.288 --> 00:11:53.376
Only.

00:11:53.312 --> 00:11:55.296
On the footing of redemption

00:11:56.384 --> 00:11:58.208
He addresses love.

00:11:57.984 --> 00:12:00.800
And grace within his holy shrine.

00:12:01.184 --> 00:12:05.184
But the basis of that shrine must be atonement.

00:12:05.952 --> 00:12:11.680
Rest assured, dear friends, that there is no meeting with God on our part.

00:12:11.840 --> 00:12:15.104
except through Jesus Christ our Redeemer.

00:12:16.160 --> 00:12:18.912
I am of Luther's mind when he said,

00:12:19.104 --> 00:12:22.944
I will have nothing to do with an absolute God.

00:12:23.456 --> 00:12:25.632
God out of Christ

00:12:25.408 --> 00:12:27.328
Is a terror to us.

00:12:27.712 --> 00:12:30.112
Even in Christ, remember.

00:12:30.016 --> 00:12:32.192
He is a consuming fire.

00:12:33.152 --> 00:12:35.936
But what he must be out of Christ,

00:12:35.872 --> 00:12:37.760
May none of us ever know.

00:12:38.624 --> 00:12:44.160
Till God in human flesh, I see my thoughts, no comfort find.

00:12:44.736 --> 00:12:45.920
The holy,

00:12:45.760 --> 00:12:46.912
Just,

00:12:46.688 --> 00:12:50.208
And sacred three are terrors to my mind.

00:12:50.272 --> 00:12:51.296
But if,

00:12:51.072 --> 00:12:53.312
Emmanuel's face appear.

00:12:53.632 --> 00:12:54.720
My hope,

00:12:54.816 --> 00:12:56.832
My joy begins.

00:12:56.832 --> 00:13:00.096
His name forbids my slavish fear.

00:13:00.032 --> 00:13:03.200
His grace removes my sins.

00:13:04.832 --> 00:13:08.928
You must not attempt to have audience with God.

00:13:08.960 --> 00:13:11.776
At first upon the footing of election.

00:13:12.448 --> 00:13:14.272
It is presumptuous.

00:13:14.144 --> 00:13:17.536
To attempt to come to the electing father.

00:13:17.280 --> 00:13:20.160
Except through the atoning son.

00:13:20.896 --> 00:13:22.080
No man,

00:13:21.856 --> 00:13:23.296
Saith Christ.

00:13:23.360 --> 00:13:25.248
Cometh to the Father,

00:13:25.312 --> 00:13:26.880
But by me.

00:13:27.360 --> 00:13:28.896
Never attempt

00:13:28.672 --> 00:13:32.832
To speak with God on the footing of your own sanctification.

00:13:33.248 --> 00:13:40.544
For very soon you will come to bringing your legal righteousness before him, and that will provoke him.

00:13:41.920 --> 00:13:45.568
Always enter the holy place with the thought

00:13:45.760 --> 00:13:48.704
I know that my redeemer lives.

00:13:49.216 --> 00:13:51.200
Not without blood.

00:13:51.200 --> 00:13:52.896
Recollect that.

00:13:53.376 --> 00:13:55.296
Into the holy place,

00:13:55.136 --> 00:13:58.272
Went the high priest once every year.

00:13:58.176 --> 00:14:00.256
Not without blood.

00:14:01.312 --> 00:14:04.640
There can be no coming of God to man.

00:14:04.672 --> 00:14:06.528
On terms of peace,

00:14:06.304 --> 00:14:09.504
Except through the one great sacrifice,

00:14:09.856 --> 00:14:12.736
That must be the foundation of it all.

00:14:14.144 --> 00:14:17.120
It is not only God's coming to us.

00:14:17.664 --> 00:14:20.384
But God's abiding with us.

00:14:20.384 --> 00:14:23.168
That is upon the same foundation.

00:14:23.776 --> 00:14:26.464
For the tabernacle was, so to speak,

00:14:26.336 --> 00:14:27.840
The house of God.

00:14:28.256 --> 00:14:35.008
The place where God especially dwelt among his people, as he said, "I will dwell in them."

00:14:34.912 --> 00:14:36.032
And walk.

00:14:35.744 --> 00:14:36.736
in them.

00:14:37.408 --> 00:14:41.408
But he never dwelt among them in anything but in a tent,

00:14:41.184 --> 00:14:42.784
That was based

00:14:42.784 --> 00:14:45.696
Upon the silver of the redemption money.

00:14:46.560 --> 00:14:48.384
And you, dear friend,

00:14:48.256 --> 00:14:51.104
If you have ever walked with God,

00:14:51.264 --> 00:14:53.984
Can only maintain your fellowship,

00:14:53.952 --> 00:14:56.960
By resting where you did at first.

00:14:56.896 --> 00:14:58.848
As a poor sinner.

00:14:58.720 --> 00:15:00.832
Redeemed by your saviour.

00:15:01.632 --> 00:15:03.680
They have asked me.

00:15:03.840 --> 00:15:06.976
To rise sometimes to a higher platform.

00:15:07.456 --> 00:15:09.152
And come to God.

00:15:08.992 --> 00:15:11.104
As a sanctified person.

00:15:11.808 --> 00:15:13.664
Yes, but a rock.

00:15:13.888 --> 00:15:18.784
Though it may be lower than the little wooden stage which some build upon it.

00:15:18.880 --> 00:15:21.312
Is safer to stand upon.

00:15:22.048 --> 00:15:23.744
And I do believe.

00:15:23.584 --> 00:15:27.808
That those who walk with God according to their attainments,

00:15:27.968 --> 00:15:30.496
And imaginary perfections

00:15:30.496 --> 00:15:36.320
Have climbed up to a rotten stage which will fall under them before long.

00:15:37.824 --> 00:15:41.792
I know no mood of standing before God today.

00:15:42.144 --> 00:15:44.992
But that which I had at first.

00:15:45.248 --> 00:15:48.608
I am unworthy still in myself.

00:15:49.056 --> 00:15:50.560
But accept it,

00:15:50.368 --> 00:15:51.680
In the beloved

00:15:52.384 --> 00:15:54.464
Guilty in myself.

00:15:54.560 --> 00:15:56.960
And lost and ruined.

00:15:57.376 --> 00:16:01.120
But still received blessed and loved

00:16:01.280 --> 00:16:04.416
Because of the person and work of christ

00:16:04.928 --> 00:16:08.288
The Lord cannot dwell with you, my dear friend.

00:16:08.096 --> 00:16:10.912
You will soon have broken fellowship.

00:16:10.688 --> 00:16:12.512
And be in the dark,

00:16:12.448 --> 00:16:17.248
If you attempt to walk with him because you feel sanctified.

00:16:17.184 --> 00:16:21.184
Or because you have been active in his service.

00:16:21.120 --> 00:16:23.296
Or because you know much.

00:16:23.360 --> 00:16:24.608
Or because

00:16:24.384 --> 00:16:27.104
You are an experienced believer.

00:16:27.008 --> 00:16:27.936
No.

00:16:27.872 --> 00:16:29.664
No, no,

00:16:30.208 --> 00:16:35.744
The Lord will only abide with us in that tabernacle whose every board,

00:16:35.520 --> 00:16:39.744
is resting upon the silver foundation of redemption.

00:16:39.808 --> 00:16:42.176
By his own dear son.

00:16:42.304 --> 00:16:49.312
Thank you for listening, friends. this podcast was brought to you by Premier in association with Spurgeon's College.

00:16:49.248 --> 00:16:52.896
For more Christian podcasts, sermons, and music,

00:16:52.768 --> 00:16:57.824
Head back to the website Premier.plus and sign in for free.

00:17:03.840 --> 00:17:13.888
Life for women can be difficult. For mothers in the Central African Republic, it's a daily struggle for survival. Imagine navigating motherhood while

00:17:13.408 --> 00:17:20.640
While facing violence, forced marriage and barriers to education for yourself and for your children.

00:17:20.448 --> 00:17:30.496
This is the reality of living in extreme poverty. With your support, Tearfund can help women learn to read and write so they can earn a living and send their children home.

00:17:30.016 --> 00:17:37.952
children to school, we're determined to end extreme poverty and injustice, following Jesus where the need is greatest.

00:17:37.760 --> 00:17:39.872
Do you have a heart to help?

00:17:39.776 --> 00:17:44.000
